        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 12:56AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1255 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Big Spring, moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Big Spring Country Club, Sand Springs, Vincent, Coahoma, Forsan, Big
Spring McMahon-Wrinkle Airpark, Luther, Elbow, and Big Spring.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 172 and 195.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
